{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":840,"text":"I believe that the secret to producing\nextremely drought-tolerant crops,"},{"time":5080,"text":"which should go some way\nto providing food security in the world,"},{"time":8320,"text":"lies in resurrection plants,"},{"time":11040,"text":"pictured here, in an extremely\ndroughted state."},{"time":14200,"text":"You might think\nthat these plants look dead,"},{"time":17080,"text":"but they're not."},{"time":18400,"text":"Give them water,"},{"time":19880,"text":"and they will resurrect, green up,\nstart growing, in 12 to 48 hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26320,"text":"Now, why would I suggest"},{"time":27640,"text":"that producing drought-tolerant crops\nwill go towards providing food security?"},{"time":33040,"text":"Well, the current world population\nis around 7 billion."},{"time":36960,"text":"And it's estimated that by 2050,"},{"time":39480,"text":"we'll be between 9 and 10 billion people,"},{"time":42200,"text":"with the bulk of this growth\nhappening in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45880,"text":"The food and agricultural\norganizations of the world"},{"time":48360,"text":"have suggested that we need\na 70 percent increase"},{"time":51520,"text":"in current agricultural practice"},{"time":53720,"text":"to meet that demand."},{"time":55720,"text":"Given that plants\nare at the base of the food chain,"},{"time":58440,"text":"most of that's going\nto have to come from plants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61360,"text":"That percentage of 70 percent"},{"time":64080,"text":"does not take into consideration\nthe potential effects of climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68320,"text":"This is taken from a study by Dai\npublished in 2011,"},{"time":73240,"text":"where he took into consideration"},{"time":75200,"text":"all the potential effects\nof climate change"},{"time":77600,"text":"and expressed them --\namongst other things --"},{"time":79760,"text":"increased aridity due to lack of rain\nor infrequent rain."},{"time":84400,"text":"The areas in red shown here,"},{"time":86200,"text":"are areas that until recently"},{"time":88280,"text":"have been very successfully\nused for agriculture,"},{"time":91480,"text":"but cannot anymore\nbecause of lack of rainfall."},{"time":94640,"text":"This is the situation\nthat's predicted to happen in 2050."},{"time":98840,"text":"Much of Africa,\nin fact, much of the world,"},{"time":101040,"text":"is going to be in trouble."},{"time":102960,"text":"We're going to have to think of some\nvery smart ways of producing food."},{"time":106640,"text":"And preferably among them,\nsome drought-tolerant crops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109960,"text":"The other thing\nto remember about Africa is"},{"time":112040,"text":"that most of their agriculture is rainfed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116080,"text":"Now, making drought-tolerant crops\nis not the easiest thing in the world."},{"time":119560,"text":"And the reason for this is water."},{"time":122000,"text":"Water is essential to life on this planet."},{"time":125160,"text":"All living, actively\nmetabolizing organisms,"},{"time":129320,"text":"from microbes to you and I,"},{"time":131400,"text":"are comprised predominately of water."},{"time":133760,"text":"All life reactions happen in water."},{"time":136320,"text":"And loss of a small amount\nof water results in death."},{"time":139360,"text":"You and I are 65 percent water --"},{"time":141440,"text":"we lose one percent of that, we die."},{"time":143840,"text":"But we can make behavioral\nchanges to avoid that."},{"time":147920,"text":"Plants can't."},{"time":149520,"text":"They're stuck in the ground."},{"time":151160,"text":"And so in the first instance they have\na little bit more water than us,"},{"time":154560,"text":"about 95 percent water,"},{"time":155840,"text":"and they can lose\na little bit more than us,"},{"time":157960,"text":"like 10 to about 70 percent,\ndepending on the species,"},{"time":162000,"text":"but for short periods only."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164680,"text":"Most of them will either try\nto resist or avoid water loss."},{"time":168880,"text":"So extreme examples of resistors\ncan be found in succulents."},{"time":172840,"text":"They tend to be small, very attractive,"},{"time":175680,"text":"but they hold onto their water\nat such great cost"},{"time":178440,"text":"that they grow extremely slowly."},{"time":181440,"text":"Examples of avoidance of water loss\nare found in trees and shrubs."},{"time":186040,"text":"They send down very deep roots,"},{"time":187640,"text":"mine subterranean water supplies"},{"time":189360,"text":"and just keep flushing\nit through them at all times,"},{"time":191840,"text":"keeping themselves hydrated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193720,"text":"The one on the right is called a baobab."},{"time":195720,"text":"It's also called the upside-down tree,"},{"time":197800,"text":"simply because the proportion\nof roots to shoots is so great"},{"time":201600,"text":"that it looks like the tree\nhas been planted upside down."},{"time":204320,"text":"And of course the roots are required\nfor hydration of that plant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208760,"text":"And probably the most common strategy\nof avoidance is found in annuals."},{"time":213840,"text":"Annuals make up the bulk\nof our plant food supplies."},{"time":217040,"text":"Up the west coast of my country,"},{"time":218760,"text":"for much of the year\nyou don't see much vegetation growth."},{"time":222320,"text":"But come the spring rains, you get this:"},{"time":225000,"text":"flowering of the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"The strategy in annuals,"},{"time":228880,"text":"is to grow only in the rainy season."},{"time":231960,"text":"At the end of that season\nthey produce a seed,"},{"time":234280,"text":"which is dry, eight to 10 percent water,"},{"time":237120,"text":"but very much alive."},{"time":238800,"text":"And anything that is\nthat dry and still alive,"},{"time":241720,"text":"we call desiccation-tolerant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243840,"text":"In the desiccated state,"},{"time":245280,"text":"what seeds can do\nis lie in extremes of environment"},{"time":247960,"text":"for prolonged periods of time."},{"time":249640,"text":"The next time the rainy season comes,"},{"time":251880,"text":"they germinate and grow,"},{"time":253400,"text":"and the whole cycle just starts again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256120,"text":"It's widely believed that the evolution\nof desiccation-tolerant seeds"},{"time":260200,"text":"allowed the colonization and the radiation"},{"time":262400,"text":"of flowering plants,\nor angiosperms, onto land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266960,"text":"But back to annuals\nas our major form of food supplies."},{"time":270800,"text":"Wheat, rice and maize form 95 percent\nof our plant food supplies."},{"time":276480,"text":"And it's been a great strategy"},{"time":278040,"text":"because in a short space of time\nyou can produce a lot of seed."},{"time":281240,"text":"Seeds are energy-rich\nso there's a lot of food calories,"},{"time":283884,"text":"you can store it in times of plenty\nfor times of famine,"},{"time":288480,"text":"but there's a downside."},{"time":290560,"text":"The vegetative tissues,"},{"time":291960,"text":"the roots and leaves of annuals,"},{"time":294160,"text":"do not have much"},{"time":295440,"text":"by way of inherent resistance,\navoidance or tolerance characteristics."},{"time":299560,"text":"They just don't need them."},{"time":300880,"text":"They grow in the rainy season"},{"time":302320,"text":"and they've got a seed\nto help them survive the rest of the year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305720,"text":"And so despite concerted\nefforts in agriculture"},{"time":308440,"text":"to make crops with improved properties"},{"time":311000,"text":"of resistance, avoidance and tolerance --"},{"time":313200,"text":"particularly resistance and avoidance"},{"time":315120,"text":"because we've had good models\nto understand how those work --"},{"time":318040,"text":"we still get images like this."},{"time":320400,"text":"Maize crop in Africa,"},{"time":321880,"text":"two weeks without rain"},{"time":323320,"text":"and it's dead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325560,"text":"There is a solution:"},{"time":327520,"text":"resurrection plants."},{"time":329320,"text":"These plants can lose 95 percent\nof their cellular water,"},{"time":333120,"text":"remain in a dry, dead-like state\nfor months to years,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and give them water,"},{"time":338760,"text":"they green up and start growing again."},{"time":341560,"text":"Like seeds, these are\ndesiccation-tolerant."},{"time":344880,"text":"Like seeds, these can withstand extremes\nof environmental conditions."},{"time":349760,"text":"And this is a really rare phenomenon."},{"time":351800,"text":"There are only 135 flowering\nplant species that can do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356200,"text":"I'm going to show you a video"},{"time":357640,"text":"of the resurrection process\nof these three species"},{"time":360280,"text":"in that order."},{"time":361520,"text":"And at the bottom,"},{"time":362800,"text":"there's a time axis\nso you can see how quickly it happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404160,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410240,"text":"Pretty amazing, huh?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":411800,"text":"So I've spent the last 21 years\ntrying to understand how they do this."},{"time":416040,"text":"How do these plants dry without dying?"},{"time":419080,"text":"And I work on a variety\nof different resurrection plants,"},{"time":421880,"text":"shown here in the hydrated and dry states,"},{"time":424320,"text":"for a number of reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425800,"text":"One of them is that each\nof these plants serves as a model"},{"time":428680,"text":"for a crop that I'd like\nto make drought-tolerant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431080,"text":"So on the extreme top left,\nfor example, is a grass,"},{"time":434040,"text":"it's called Eragrostis nindensis,"},{"time":436320,"text":"it's got a close relative\ncalled Eragrostis tef --"},{"time":438720,"text":"a lot of you might know it as \"teff\" --"},{"time":440760,"text":"it's a staple food in Ethiopia,"},{"time":442520,"text":"it's gluten-free,"},{"time":443800,"text":"and it's something we would like\nto make drought-tolerant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446840,"text":"The other reason for looking\nat a number of plants,"},{"time":449280,"text":"is that, at least initially,"},{"time":450680,"text":"I wanted to find out:\ndo they do the same thing?"},{"time":452960,"text":"Do they all use the same mechanisms"},{"time":454680,"text":"to be able to lose\nall that water and not die?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457280,"text":"So I undertook what we call\na systems biology approach"},{"time":460000,"text":"in order to get\na comprehensive understanding"},{"time":462200,"text":"of desiccation tolerance,"},{"time":464240,"text":"in which we look at everything"},{"time":465720,"text":"from the molecular to the whole plant,\necophysiological level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468657,"text":"For example we look at things like"},{"time":470316,"text":"changes in the plant anatomy\nas they dried out"},{"time":472537,"text":"and their ultrastructure."},{"time":473800,"text":"We look at the transcriptome,\nwhich is just a term for a technology"},{"time":477000,"text":"in which we look at the genes"},{"time":478440,"text":"that are switched on or off,\nin response to drying."},{"time":480880,"text":"Most genes will code for proteins,\nso we look at the proteome."},{"time":484120,"text":"What are the proteins made\nin response to drying?"},{"time":487480,"text":"Some proteins would code for enzymes\nwhich make metabolites,"},{"time":491400,"text":"so we look at the metabolome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"Now, this is important\nbecause plants are stuck in the ground."},{"time":496320,"text":"They use what I call\na highly tuned chemical arsenal"},{"time":500440,"text":"to protect themselves from all\nthe stresses of their environment."},{"time":503880,"text":"So it's important that we look"},{"time":505400,"text":"at the chemical changes\ninvolved in drying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508520,"text":"And at the last study\nthat we do at the molecular level,"},{"time":511200,"text":"we look at the lipidome --"},{"time":512480,"text":"the lipid changes in response to drying."},{"time":514559,"text":"And that's also important"},{"time":515840,"text":"because all biological membranes\nare made of lipids."},{"time":518679,"text":"They're held as membranes\nbecause they're in water."},{"time":521280,"text":"Take away the water,\nthose membranes fall apart."},{"time":524240,"text":"Lipids also act as signals\nto turn on genes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528200,"text":"Then we use physiological\nand biochemical studies"},{"time":530920,"text":"to try and understand\nthe function of the putative protectants"},{"time":534160,"text":"that we've actually discovered\nin our other studies."},{"time":537120,"text":"And then use all of that\nto try and understand"},{"time":539320,"text":"how the plant copes\nwith its natural environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543480,"text":"I've always had the philosophy that\nI needed a comprehensive understanding"},{"time":547840,"text":"of the mechanisms of desiccation tolerance"},{"time":550120,"text":"in order to make a meaningful suggestion\nfor a biotic application."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555000,"text":"I'm sure some of you are thinking,"},{"time":556680,"text":"\"By biotic application,"},{"time":557960,"text":"does she mean she's going to make\ngenetically modified crops?\""},{"time":562240,"text":"And the answer to that question is:"},{"time":563960,"text":"depends on your definition\nof genetic modification."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567200,"text":"All of the crops that we eat today,\nwheat, rice and maize,"},{"time":570040,"text":"are highly genetically modified\nfrom their ancestors,"},{"time":573280,"text":"but we don't consider them GM"},{"time":575280,"text":"because they're being produced\nby conventional breeding."},{"time":578880,"text":"If you mean, am I going to put\nresurrection plant genes into crops,"},{"time":582680,"text":"your answer is yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"In the essence of time,\nwe have tried that approach."},{"time":587160,"text":"More appropriately,\nsome of my collaborators at UCT,"},{"time":590040,"text":"Jennifer Thomson, Suhail Rafudeen,"},{"time":592000,"text":"have spearheaded that approach"},{"time":593640,"text":"and I'm going to show you some data soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597200,"text":"But we're about to embark\nupon an extremely ambitious approach,"},{"time":601240,"text":"in which we aim to turn on\nwhole suites of genes"},{"time":604720,"text":"that are already present in every crop."},{"time":607440,"text":"They're just never turned on\nunder extreme drought conditions."},{"time":610800,"text":"I leave it up to you to decide"},{"time":612280,"text":"whether those should be called GM or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615560,"text":"I'm going to now just give you\nsome of the data from that first approach."},{"time":619040,"text":"And in order to do that"},{"time":620320,"text":"I have to explain a little bit\nabout how genes work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"So you probably all know"},{"time":624280,"text":"that genes are made\nof double-stranded DNA."},{"time":626360,"text":"It's wound very tightly into chromosomes"},{"time":628320,"text":"that are present in every cell\nof your body or in a plant's body."},{"time":632080,"text":"If you unwind that DNA, you get genes."},{"time":635840,"text":"And each gene has a promoter,"},{"time":638320,"text":"which is just an on-off switch,"},{"time":640720,"text":"the gene coding region,"},{"time":642160,"text":"and then a terminator,"},{"time":643440,"text":"which indicates that this is the end\nof this gene, the next gene will start."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647720,"text":"Now, promoters are not\nsimple on-off switches."},{"time":650640,"text":"They normally require\na lot of fine-tuning,"},{"time":653360,"text":"lots of things to be present and correct\nbefore that gene is switched on."},{"time":658240,"text":"So what's typically done\nin biotech studies"},{"time":661320,"text":"is that we use an inducible promoter,"},{"time":663160,"text":"we know how to switch it on."},{"time":664760,"text":"We couple that to genes of interest"},{"time":666800,"text":"and put that into a plant\nand see how the plant responds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670120,"text":"In the study that I'm going\nto talk to you about,"},{"time":672720,"text":"my collaborators used\na drought-induced promoter,"},{"time":675200,"text":"which we discovered\nin a resurrection plant."},{"time":677640,"text":"The nice thing about this promoter\nis that we do nothing."},{"time":680800,"text":"The plant itself senses drought."},{"time":683600,"text":"And we've used it to drive antioxidant\ngenes from resurrection plants."},{"time":688720,"text":"Why antioxidant genes?"},{"time":690600,"text":"Well, all stresses,\nparticularly drought stress,"},{"time":693680,"text":"results in the formation of free radicals,"},{"time":696000,"text":"or reactive oxygen species,"},{"time":698360,"text":"which are highly damaging\nand can cause crop death."},{"time":701680,"text":"What antioxidants do is stop that damage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705360,"text":"So here's some data from a maize strain\nthat's very popularly used in Africa."},{"time":709280,"text":"To the left of the arrow\nare plants without the genes,"},{"time":712600,"text":"to the right --"},{"time":713880,"text":"plants with the antioxidant genes."},{"time":715960,"text":"After three weeks without watering,"},{"time":717800,"text":"the ones with the genes\ndo a hell of a lot better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721720,"text":"Now to the final approach."},{"time":723080,"text":"My research has shown\nthat there's considerable similarity"},{"time":726640,"text":"in the mechanisms of desiccation tolerance\nin seeds and resurrection plants."},{"time":731080,"text":"So I ask the question,"},{"time":732520,"text":"are they using the same genes?"},{"time":734480,"text":"Or slightly differently phrased,"},{"time":736760,"text":"are resurrection plants using genes\nevolved in seed desiccation tolerance"},{"time":741280,"text":"in their roots and leaves?"},{"time":742560,"text":"Have they retasked these seed genes"},{"time":744640,"text":"in roots and leaves\nof resurrection plants?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":747760,"text":"And I answer that question,"},{"time":749640,"text":"as a consequence of a lot\nof research from my group"},{"time":752080,"text":"and recent collaborations from a group\nof Henk Hilhorst in the Netherlands,"},{"time":755640,"text":"Mel Oliver in the United States"},{"time":757240,"text":"and Julia Buitink in France."},{"time":759880,"text":"The answer is yes,"},{"time":761320,"text":"that there is a core set of genes\nthat are involved in both."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764200,"text":"And I'm going to illustrate this\nvery crudely for maize,"},{"time":767640,"text":"where the chromosomes below the off switch"},{"time":770080,"text":"represent all the genes that are required\nfor desiccation tolerance."},{"time":773680,"text":"So as maize seeds dried out\nat the end of their period of development,"},{"time":777960,"text":"they switch these genes on."},{"time":780680,"text":"Resurrection plants\nswitch on the same genes"},{"time":783600,"text":"when they dry out."},{"time":785280,"text":"All modern crops, therefore,"},{"time":787080,"text":"have these genes\nin their roots and leaves,"},{"time":789160,"text":"they just never switch them on."},{"time":790920,"text":"They only switch them on in seed tissues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793440,"text":"So what we're trying to do right now"},{"time":795200,"text":"is to understand the environmental\nand cellular signals"},{"time":797840,"text":"that switch on these genes\nin resurrection plants,"},{"time":801280,"text":"to mimic the process in crops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803680,"text":"And just a final thought."},{"time":805440,"text":"What we're trying to do very rapidly"},{"time":807680,"text":"is to repeat what nature did\nin the evolution of resurrection plants"},{"time":811520,"text":"some 10 to 40 million years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814160,"text":"My plants and I thank you\nfor your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816680,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}